    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n3200" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐν-οπή</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὄψ</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">voice</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            10.147</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">outcry;</span> attributed to musical
          instruments, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αὐλῶν σῡρίγγων τ᾽ ἐνοπήν</span>,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 10.13</span></i>; esp. of the cry of
          battle, <i><span class="en">Il. 3.2</span></i>, and figuratively for
          battle itself, <i><span class="en">Il. 12.35</span></i>; of grief,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐνοπήν τε γόον τε</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 24.160</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
